The Head of Funsengbuwa Ruling House, Otunba Olasubomi Balogun, has put an end to the rumours flying round that he’s interested in Ijebuland kingship. Subomi, who is the Akile Ijebu denied this during the annual general meeting of the Arojojoye ruling house of Ijebuland held at Fusengbuwa Family Museum, Ijebu-Ode, Ogun State on Monday. He said: “I have no interest in Ijebuland kingship. Awujale of Ijebuland, Dr Sikiru Kayode Adetona, is still alive and we must fear God. Buhari has taken Nigeria close to Next Level target ― Lai… Wike signs Rivers 2020 budget Trump, Putin discuss Russia attack, arms control, relations Seven killed in Edo communal clash ALSO READ: BREAKING: Sokoto lawmaker dies at 55 “I’m contented with what I have and none of my children is eyeing any kingship even though they are males but we are okay with what we have. It is a taboo in Yorubaland to be scheming for Oba’s successor when a reigning monarch is still alive. “Awujale happens to be my friend and he’s the one that named me as Olori Omooba in 1985 and I will never harm my fellow human being,” he said. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
